Value: Red Hill Iron Limited engages in the exploration of iron ore, gold, and base metals in Western Australia. The company's primary assets are the 40% owned Red Hill Iron Ore Joint Venture (RHIOJV) interest; wholly owned Pannawonica channel iron project; and its 100% non-ferrous metal exploration interests over the RHIOJV tenements. It also has quarrying opportunities in the Pannawonica region. The company was incorporated in 2005 and is based in West Perth, Australia.
